In absence of a simple model available that accounts for the presence of surfactants and with the aim to find an appropriate timescale, let us consider a drainage flow dominated by viscous shear, balanced either by gravity or capillarity. Starting with a gravity-driven drainage, the momentum balance at leading order in the lubrication approximation writes7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
